The paper deals with reverse engineering of data formats, which is a common problem in computer security (cs.CR) and database systems (cs.DB). The formalization of the unshuffling problem and the probabilistic bounds suggest a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), while the empirical demonstration and connections with synchronization problems suggest a potential overlap with machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT).
